Package seng202.group2.view.graphs

Class Graph

java.lang.Object
seng202.group2.view.graphs.Graph
Direct Known Subclasses:
BarGraph, LineGraph, ScatterGraph
public abstract class Graph
extends java.lang.Object
A superclass specifying all methods which a Graph type must implement in order to interface with control classes. Some utility methods are provided for getting a set of the Class objects of all Graph subtypes within this package, using reflection.
Author:
Connor Dunlop

    • optionStatesValid

      public boolean optionStatesValid()
      Checks that all GraphOptions are in a valid state for plotting. I.e. checks that all required options are in a valid configuration.
      Returns:
      False if any options are in an invalid state for plotting, true if all options are in a valid state.
